        "type": "paragraph",
        "snippet": "Reunification counselling in Vancouver, BC, varies significantly in cost depending on whether it is court-ordered, privately funded, or accessed through community services, with private sessions generally ranging from $135 to over $300 per session. Boomerang Counselling Centre +1",
        "reference_indexes": [
          0,
          2,
          11,
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "snippet": "Key Cost Breakdown for Vancouver:"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "list": [
          {
            "snippet": "MCFD-Referred Services (Free): Families referred by a Ministry of Children and Family Development (MCFD) social worker for child protection concerns can access no-fee Family Preservation and Reunification Services through agencies like Family Services of Greater Vancouver."
          },
          {
            "snippet": "Private Practice Registered Clinical Counsellors (RCC):",
            "list": [
              {
                "snippet": "50-minute session: $140\u2013$220."
              },
              {
                "snippet": "75-minute session: ~$250\u2013$300."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "snippet": "Specialized High-Conflict/Reunification Programs: These can be very expensive, with some specialized programs requiring high retainers ($35,000+) or specialized, multi-professional, high-hourly rates."
          },
          {
            "snippet": "Reduced-Cost/Sliding Scale: Some organizations and interns offer lower rates, typically ranging from $30 to $110 per session depending on income. Reddit +8"
          }
        ],
        "reference_indexes": [
          2,
          0,
          1,
          3,
          5,
          7,
          9,
          10,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "snippet": "Factors Affecting Price:"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "list": [
          {
            "snippet": "Duration: 75-minute sessions are more expensive than 50-minute sessions."
          },
          {
            "snippet": "Expertise: Higher fees are often charged for doctoral-level professionals or specialized therapists."
          },
          {
            "snippet": "Court Involvement: Cases involving court-ordered therapists may involve additional costs for reports, legal coordination, and meetings. Reddit +2"
          }
        ],
        "reference_indexes": [
          1,
          0,
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "snippet": "It is recommended to check if your extended health benefits plan covers Registered Clinical Counsellors (RCCs), Registered Social Workers (RSWs), or Psychologists. Youthwise Counselling",
